caption: b'#Prada, in collaboration with @theofficialselfridges, presents the new #PradaHoliday pop-up store, a magical space dedicated to exclusive gifts for men and women during the #Holiday period.\n\nThe pop up is open at #Selfridges London from December 2 \xe2\x80\x93 January 10.'

b'On December 3, #Prada received the \xe2\x80\x982020 Fashion Awards\xe2\x80\x99 under the Creativity category during a digital celebration of the annual #FashionAwards, presented by the @britishfashioncouncil.\nPrada has been recognized as a brand that embodies what a modern luxury house is about, creativity and social responsibility. \nCo-Creative directors #MiucciaPrada and #RafSimons received the prize as they created positive change within the fashion industry this year, demonstrating the power of creativity and the importance of conversations through their first show together last September.'

b'Introducing the #adidasforPrada A+P Luna Rossa 21. Fueled by a dedication to innovation and sustainability and crafted with sport performance at its core, this sailing-inspired silhouette features expertly engineered PRIMEGREEN, a series of high-performance recycled materials. The shoes have been designed for the #LunaRossaPradaPirelli team.
Serving as the next evolution of this forward-thinking partnership, the adidas for Prada A+P LUNA ROSSA 21 silhouette launches globally in a white colorway on December 9 2020, via Prada boutiques and adidas flagship stores worldwide, alongside selected wholesalers. The range is also available via prada.com and adidas.com.
Link in bio.

b'#Prada presents the new #PradaEnchanted pop-up store, a magical and fascinating space dedicated to precious gifts for men and women in view of the Holiday period, at @thedubaimall.\nThe space, located in the Fashion Catwalk, is defined by a multifaceted glass structure, decorated with triangle motifs that refer to the iconic Prada logo.\nThe idea of the installation is characterized by the combination of a double shade: black for the external facade that graphically outlines the central space and the classic Prada green for the interior, in order to offer a relaxing atmosphere that distinguishes the image of Prada boutiques in the world.'

b'With the support of @fondazioneprada, in #PradaRongZhai, #AlexDaCorte presents #RubberPencilDevil a video work inspired by a wide range of iconographical and cultural sources from vintage television imagery to 20th-century animation.\nThe project will be on view from 13 November 2020 to 17 January 2021 in the premises of the historical residence in Shanghai restored by #Prada and reopened in October 2017.\nLink in bio.'

b'With the support of @fondazioneprada #RubberPencilDevil is conceived as a dream-like journey where #AlexDaCorte\xe2\x80\x99s intellectually, provocative, exuberant and absurd fantasies provide a critical take on contemporary reality, but also create \xe2\x80\x9cnew ideas and new beginnings\xe2\x80\x9d.\nThe project will be on view from 13 November 2020 to 17 January 2021 in the premises of #PradaRongZhai in Shanghai.\nLink in bio.'

b'With the support of @fondazioneprada, #RubberPencilDevil represents #AlexDaCorte himself, who mutates into various food puppets and iconic characters such as Pink Panther, Sylvester the Cat and Bugs Bunny immersed in a universe composed of everyday objects, domestic symbols and familiar codes.\nThe project will be on view from 13 November 2020 to 17 January 2021 in the premises of #PradaRongZhai in Shanghai.\nDiscover all the artworks via link in bio.'

b'With the support of @fondazioneprada #Prada presents #RubberPencilDevil, an immersive experience combining video, music and architecture where #AlexDaCorte explores themes of alienation and human desire with a subversive humour and a psychological introspection.\nThe project will be on view from 13 November 2020 to 17 January 2021 in the premises of #PradaRongZhai in Shanghai.\nLink in bio.'

b'Guests #DuJuan, @chen_wenqi, @zhaozhaolei, @huang__jue, @xixihaha_dex, #LiaoFan, #QiXi, #RongZishan, #SongJia, #ZhaoTao arriving at #PradaMode Shanghai experience "Mia\xcc\x80n", a site-specific intervention by filmmaker #JiaZhangke that bridges historical and contemporary art and architecture. \nDiscover more via link in bio.\n#PradaRongZhai'

b'For the fifth #PradaMode, filmmaker #JiaZhangke takes over the historic #PradaRongZhai in Shanghai with a multi-chapter intervention titled Mi\xc3\xa0n\xe2\x80\x94a word with many meanings. A 1980s-era video hall, a 1990s-style Chinese Disco, and cinematic fine dining create a few of the layers between the early 20th century mansion and the 3-day event\xe2\x80\x99s contemporary programming.
 
\xe2\x80\x9cThe word Mi\xc3\xa0n has over a dozen meanings in the Chinese dictionary,\xe2\x80\x9d Jia writes. \xe2\x80\x9cIt can mean processed food made from flour, a trajectory formed by a moving line in geometry, a meeting, the surface of a person\xe2\x80\x99s face...\xe2\x80\x9d
 
Discover more via link in bio.

#PradaModeShanghai'

b'#PradaSS21 collection focuses on the quintessence of Prada, the meaning. How clothes are worn, where, and why. b'#TerenceNance (@terenceetc) on creating Chapter 5 of #PradaMultipleViews, the show that never happened: 
"The film that came through was born of speed and play; I have no words through which to decode what the meaning is and was and will\xc2\xa0be, but it may be about time\xe2\x80\x94and keeping your organs in that vessel we call a body while it contorts itself to love each second as it goes bye-bye."
Watch the full show on IGTV or prada.com.
#PradaSS21'

b'#MartineSyms on creating Chapter 4 of #PradaMultipleViews, the show that never happened: 
"The video is a collage of multiple formats and features iterative, repetitive movements intercut with beautiful people staring at images of themselves on monitors and screens in Milan and in my studio in Los Angeles. Since the collection pieces have a '60s feeling to them, I tried to include several references to cinema culture and surveillance/sousveillance from that time period and the present. I'm inspired by the way screens have come to make and unmake us\xe2\x80\x94and what it means to be living, breathing, moving, fleshy things in a world full of them."
Watch the full show on IGTV or prada.com.
#PradaSS21'

b'#JoannaPiotrowska on creating Chapter 3 of #PradaMultipleViews, the show that never happened: 
"Gesture and physicality are an essential non-verbal form of communication and play a big role in the conceptual and compositional aspects of my work. The finger snap is a quick and subtle, yet attention-demanding action. It is also used to indicate approval or to maintain rhythm. I thought that this short could be an interesting space to work with the snap as a recurring motif that marks the movements and refocuses the viewer\xe2\x80\x99s attention to each new look."
Watch the full show on IGTV or prada.com.
#PradaSS21'

b'#JuergenTeller on creating Chapter 2 of #PradaMultipleViews, the show that never happened: 
"\xe2\x80\x98It was an honor to be asked to photograph and film Miuccia\xe2\x80\x98s last collection. I thought the men and women looked beautiful, elegant and modern. I enjoyed looking at Miuccia\xe2\x80\x98s vision and trying to make sense of it as honestly and directly as possible."
Watch the full show on IGTV or prada.com.
#PradaSS21'

b'@WillyVanderperre on creating Chapter 1 of #PradaMultipleViews, the show that never happened: 
"Prada evolves and changes every season, this season, the part we were shooting and filming felt like an honest collection. Stripped from fashion ideas, which turns that idea into fashion again. It also felt introspective and slightly schizophrenic. A look into the past with the future ahead. I hope that the audience feels that in the movie, a distilled pure and honest presentation of the collection."
Watch the full show on IGTV or prada.com.
#PradaSS21'

The discussion took place on #InstagramLive on May 12 at 6pm CET (12pm ET). Now on IGTV. \nWith each live conversation in this series, #Prada will donate to @UNESCO \xe2\x80\x93 an organization whose work during the #covid19 pandemic focuses on over 1.5 billion students worldwide who have been affected by school closure. \xe2\xa0\x80\nDiscover more via link in bio.'

b'Unveiled in October 2017 after 6 years of meticulous #RestorationWorks by Italian and Chinese craftsmen, Prada Rong Zhai is a historic mansion reimagined as a flexible site for the Group\xe2\x80\x99s cultural activities. This architecture expresses the dialogue between the cities of Milan and Shanghai and #PradaGroup\xe2\x80\x99s admiration for the Chinese aesthetic heritage. Find out more via link in bio. #Remix'

b'Each time #PradaGroup opened a store in Italy, it supported local #RestorationWorks and value enhancement projects through a long-term collaboration with @fondoambiente FAI - Fondo Ambiente Italiano (the National Trust for Italy). Each initiative, chosen with great care, enabled us to give back to the community precious elements of its artistic heritage in cities like Florence, Turin, Bari, Padua and Bologna. #Remix'

b'Welcome to the second episode of #Remix, a series of dynamic content to discover the #PradaGroup\xe2\x80\x99s DNA in an unexpected way. #RestorationWorks tells the story of our commitment and mastery to preserve artistic heritage. The renovation of the Galleria, the Milanese arcade hosting Prada\xe2\x80\x99s historical store, symbolises this pledge: 14,000 sqm restored over a period of 13 months to bring back this unique monument to its original beauty, 150 years after its first stone was laid. Link in bio.'

b'Colors are extreme,
fabrications surreal in their incongruity. Throughout, nevertheless, there is an innate, palpable reality - a sense of the indomitability of humanity, of nature, of the continuation of life. Clothing mirrors the pluralism and complexity of female identities - of women embodying multiple ideas of the \xe2\x80\x98self\xe2\x80\x99, simultaneously. They defy any simplistic categorization - they reflect the everfluctuating rapport of women with their own identities.

b"After ascending a grand staircase, guests enter the #PradaFW20 Womenswear show space on a raised platform overlooking two identical voids, each containing the same fictional courtyard.
The scene is simple yet dynamic: a series of portals organized symmetrically around the courts mark a threshold between inside and outside. At the center of each composition is a statue of Atlas abstracted into a series of sliding and interlocking planes.
See the #PradaFW20 Womenswear show by #MiucciaPrada live today, Thursday \xe2\x81\xa3February \xe2\x81\xa320th at 4pm CEST, on \xe2\x81\xa3#Prada's \xe2\x81\xa3#instagram.\xe2\xa0\x80
#mfw"

b'#PradaMode is a traveling social club with a focus on contemporary culture from local to global. So far, it has taken place in Miami Beach, Hong Kong, London, and Paris as an extension of and dialogue with large-scale art events in those enigmatic cities. Where will it occur next?

b'@IddrisSandu spent 48 hours at #PradaModeParis exploring art projects and data visualizations by AI Researcher Kate Crawford and Artist / Researcher Trevor Paglen.

The works of art showcased not only challenged his design thinking to observe beyond the surface bias-is of facial recognition and data gathering ; but to also think deeper into how such technologies could be utilized to usher in new forms of art. All while connecting people together on both an empathetic and emotional level.

Watched the mind - packed two day program on #Prada IGTV.'

b'For the occasion of #PradaMode Paris at @maxims.de.paris, AI researcher, composer, and academic @__KateCrawford__ and artist, geographer, and author @TrevorPaglen have installed \xe2\x80\x9cMaking Faces,\xe2\x80\x9d an interactive exhibition investigating surveillance, big data, and identity detection.
